# Pattern: "bad metric" (lower is better) — bounded percentage.
# Illustrates: no-change-threshold flexibility, multi-source funnel with strict lower/upper range.
Metric: Cart Abandonment Rate
Description: Percentage of shopping carts created in the last 24 hours that were never checked out.
Owner: ecommerce-team
Tags: ecommerce, funnel, weekly-review

Source: carts, checkouts

Given all carts created in the last 24 hours
  And the cart has at least one item
  And the user is not an internal test account

When we calculate
  Then count carts without a matching checkout record
  And divide by total carts created in the same window
  And multiply by 100 to get a percentage

The result is "Cart Abandonment Rate"

Trust:
  Freshness must be less than 2 hours
  Null rate on cart_id must be 0%
  Null rate on user_id must be less than 1%
  Row count must not drop more than 30% day over day
  Value must be between 40 and 85
  Value must not change more than 10% week over week
